### Describe the bug
I want to replace an existing application with a Blazor Serverside application but existing url's need to keep working. I want to rewrite url's using custom middleware so the Blazor applications is build like it should. 

When i change the request path using middleware the blazor page is not shown correctly. It is shown very briefly and then the NotFound content is show. This is behaviour i cannot explain.

### To Reproduce
Create a new Blazor Server project and add this middleware below app.UseStaticFiles() in Startup.cs

` 
    app.Use(async (context, next) => 
    {
        if(context.Request.Path == "/a")
        {
            context.Request.Path = "/";
        }
        await next();
    });
`

If you start the application and visit / the welcome page is show. If you visit /a the welcome page is shown briefly and than the NotFound layout is shown. 

### Further technical details
This exists both in .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0

